8 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 8-103.1, as amended by Section 2, Chapter
9 451, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 8-
103.1), which relates to interdistrict transfers;
10 requiring school districts to accept students of
active duty military families on official orders;
11 removing district residency requirements for students
of active duty military families; requiring schools
12 to treat students of military families as in-district
residents for enrollment purposes; providing an
13 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 8-103.1, as
17 amended by Section 2, Chapter 451, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
18 Section 8-103.1), is amended to read as follows:
19 Section 8-103.1. A. A local school district board of education
20 which receives a request for a transfer for a student who does not
21 reside in the school district may refuse the transfer in accordance
22 with the provisions of the open transfer policy adopted by the local
23 school district board of education and subject to the provisions of
24 subsections B and C of this section. Each local board of education
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4274 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 shal l adopt an open transfer policy for the school district which
2 specifies its criteria and standards for approval of transfers of
3 students who do not reside in the district. The policy shall
4 include, but shall not be limited to, provisions relating to the
5 availability of programs, staff, or space as criteria for approval
6 or denial of transfers. A school district may include in the policy
7 as the basis for denial of a transfer, the reasons outlined in
8 Section 24-101.3 of this title.
9 In considering requests for students to transfer into a school
10 district, the board of education shall consider the requests on a
11 first-come, first-serve basis. A school district shall not accept
12 or deny a transfer based on ethnicity, national origin, gender,
13 income level, disabling condition, proficiency in the English
14 language, measure of achievement, aptitude, or athletic ability.
15 Notwithstanding the provisions of the Education Open Transfer
16 Act, transfers of children with disabilities shall be granted as
17 authorized in Section 13-103 of this title.
18 B. A local school district board of education shall adopt a
19 policy for the school district regarding the transfer of students
20 Students who are the dependent children of a member of the active
21 uniformed military services of the United States on full-time active
22 duty status and students who are the dependent children of a member
23 of the military reserve on active duty orders shall be eligible for
24 admission to the school district of their choice if he or she is a
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4274 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 stud ent whose parent or legal guardian is transferred or is pending
2 transfer to a military installation within the state while on active
3 military duty pursuant to an official military order. The policy
4 shall provide for the approval of the transfer if:
5 1. At Students shall be eligible if at least one parent of the
6 student has a Department of Defense-issued identification card; and
7 2. The student will be residing with a relative of the student
8 who lives in the receiving school district or who will be living in
9 the receiving school district within six (6) months of the filing of
10 the application for transfer.
11 C. 1. A student shall be considered in compliance with the
12 residency provisions of Section 1-113 of this title if he or she is
13 a student whose parent or legal guardian is transferred or is
14 pending transfer to a military installation within the state while
15 on active military duty pursuant to an official military order.
16 2. A school district shall accept applications by electronic
17 means for enrollment including enrollment in a specific school or
18 program within the school district and course registration for
19 students described in paragraph 1 of this subsection.
20 3. Students described in subsection B of this section who
21 currently reside outside of a district they are transferring to
22 shall be treated by the receiving district as residing within the
23 receiving district for purposes of enrollment.
24
